    "reasoning": "To implement the given FSM, I first identify the states and their transitions based on the provided state diagram. The FSM has four states: A, B, C, and D. State A is the initial state where no requests are active. From state A, the FSM transitions to different states based on the input r. The transitions involve checking combinations of r[0], r[1], and r[2]. I will use binary encoding for states (e.g., A=00, B=01, C=10, D=11). I also define priority for the request signals: r[0] has highest priority, then r[1], then r[2]. In the state transition logic, I'll determine the next state based on current state and input. For the output logic, I'll ensure that g[0], g[1], and g[2] are set according to which device gets the grant. Using separate always blocks for state flip-flops and next state logic ensures correct timing behavior. Since reset is active low and synchronous, I'll reset the state register to A on reset assertion. I also make sure that all signals are declared as logic, and use proper assignment syntax.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input resetn,\n    input [2:0] r,\n    output [2:0] g\n);\n\n    // State definitions\n    localparam ST_A = 2'b00;\n    localparam ST_B = 2'b01;\n    localparam ST_C = 2'b10;\n    localparam ST_D = 2'b11;\n\n    // Current and next state\n    logic [1:0] state, next_state;\n\n    // Next state logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            ST_A: begin\n                if (r[0])\n                    next_state = ST_B;\n                else if (r[1])\n                    next_state = ST_C;\n                else if (r[2])\n                    next_state = ST_D;\n                else\n                    next_state = ST_A;\n            end\n            \n            ST_B: begin\n                if (r[0])\n                    next_state = ST_B;\n                else\n                    next_state = ST_A;\n            end\n            \n            ST_C: begin\n                if (r[1])\n                    next_state = ST_C;\n                else\n                    next_state = ST_A;\n            end\n            \n            ST_D: begin\n                next_state = ST_D;\n            end\n            \n            default: next_state = ST_A;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // State flip-flop\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (!resetn)\n            state <= ST_A;\n        else\n            state <= next_state;\n    end\n\n    // Output logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            ST_A: g = 3'b000;\n            ST_B: g = 3'b001;\n            ST_C: g = 3'b010;\n            ST_D: g = 3'b100;\n            default: g = 3'b000;\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
